I"°	<h1 id="three-keys-to-influencing-people">Three keys to influencing people</h1>
<ol>
  <li>Make the message understandable
    <ul>
      <li>Tell a story that clearly and concisely explains what you want to do</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Show the value
    <ul>
      <li>Begin by showing that you understand their needs</li>
      <li>Then show how you can achieve those goals</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Be authentic
    <ul>
      <li>You want to be trusted</li>
      <li>Donâ€™t try to be slick or smooth, just be confident in yourself</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<h1 id="emotional-intelligence">Emotional intelligence</h1>
<p>Twice as important as IQ and technical skills; even more so in
management</p>

<ol>
  <li>Self-awareness
    <ul>
      <li>Understanding your own emotions and their effects on others</li>
      <li>Can talk about personal strengths and weaknesses; often
self-deprecating</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Self-regulation
    <ul>
      <li>Being able to control disruptive impulses</li>
      <li>Thinking before acting</li>
      <li>More open to change</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Motivation
    <ul>
      <li>Being goal-oriented, optimistic and committed</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Empathy
    <ul>
      <li>Understanding the emotional needs of others</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Social skill
    <ul>
      <li>Proficiency in managing relationships, developing networks, building
rapport and finding common ground</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<h1 id="how-successful-people-reach-their-goals">How successful people reach their goals</h1>

<ol>
  <li>Get specific about what you want to achieve</li>
  <li>Decide where and when you will act on your goals
    <ul>
      <li>Blocking-out time on your calendar is very effective!</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Shift your mindset
    <ul>
      <li>Focus on what you <em>will</em> do, not what you <em>wonâ€™t</em> do</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<h1 id="craft-a-story-to-sell-your-written-business-case">Craft a story to sell your (written) business case</h1>
<p>Winning cases tell memorable and compelling stories</p>

<ol>
  <li>Identify a strategic need or opportunity
    <ul>
      <li>Show how your idea supports these needs</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Lay out the projectâ€™s approach</li>
  <li>Describe <em>specific</em> costs and benefits
    <ul>
      <li>Eg: â€œreduce product returns by 10%, saving Â£30,000</li>
      <li>Summarise these values</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>
